		<td><b>Super Glove Ball Hack</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Before I even start, I should say I already PM'd the creator of this hack about this, but figured others might have some valuable input as well.<br /><br />I have a Famicom Power glove that is going into an NES that is modded to have a Famicom EXP port. The Power glove works fine with every game I try except for Super Glove Ball, which being a US release, did not have support for the Famicom EXP port. I have modified the ROM to allow the Famicom EXP port to be used and it works off of my Everdrive now with the glove, however during seemingly random moments, the screen blanks out and comes back and I see some graphical bugs at the bottom for a split moment, then things return to normal. If this was once every once in awhile, I could deal, but it happens too often and ruins the game. Is there any hope of getting this issue to stop or should I just invest in a US glove instead (or maybe a Famicom...). It should be noted that my Everdrive is a Chinese one and although I've never had an issue with that fact, in theory it *could* be related.<br />Seriously any suggestions would be helpful. Cheers!

		
