	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Super Glove Ball Hack</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Okay, so I know this topic really only effects like... 3 people ever at most.. BUT. I fixed this issue. I wrote at least a dozen or so patches for this game to make it work with the J glove with no luck until I caught on today that the music reset to a previous point in the game when the flashes occurred. Well.. This clued me into the fact that the game was moving between points in time I.E. states. My flash cart (Everdrive N8) apparently supports save states, which I was unaware of. The issue here is that the input read by the &quot;center&quot; button on the Power Glove happens to trigger the save state combo and the load state gets triggered through the various movements involved in Super Glove Ball. <br /><br /><br />Long story short: Disable save stating on your Everdrive N8 with the patch made by Rainwarrior and you will be able to play this game flawlessly with a Japanese Power glove assuming you have either A.) A European Famicom or B.) An American NES modded to take in the Famicom EXP port as input. I sincerely hope this helps one of you dodge this issue in the future. Thanks to any of those that put any degree of thought or input into this thread.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


